HEADWORD: Telerythin
<hw>Tel`e*ryth"in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ end +
E. <ets>erythrin</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A red crystalline
compound related to, or produced from, erythrin. So called because
regarded as the end of the series of erythrin compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

